laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Ultrasound of Liver or Gallbladder (Single Organ)

findings.liver: The hepatic parenchyma appears within normal limits. The contour of the liver is smooth. There is no focal liver mass.
findings.bile_ducts: There is no intrahepatic biliary dilation.
findings.gallbladder: There are stones and sludge in a distended gallbladder. There is a positive sonographic ___ sign. There may be trace pericholecystic fluid. No mural edema.
findings.pancreas: The head and body of the pancreas are within normal limits. The tail of the pancreas is not visualized due to the presence of gas.
findings.kidneys: Limited views of the kidneys show no hydronephrosis. Right kidney: 12.5 cm, Left kidney: 11.7 cm.
findings.retroperitoneum: The visualized portions of aorta and IVC are within normal limits.

laboratory_examinations.findings: STAPHYLOCOCCUS, COAGULASE NEGATIVE - 13.0 ug/mL (Normal range: 10.0 - 20.0 ug/mL)
